\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 30. A. sagittatum} (DC.) Bange, {\i Bull. Soc. Linn. Lyon }{\b 21:} 84 (1952) ({\i Phyllitis sagittata} (DC.) Guinea & Heywood,{\i  P. hemionitis} (Swartz) O. Kuntze, {\i Scolopendrium hemionitis} (Swartz) Lag.). Leaves 12-30 cm, tufted, persistent; petiole ½ as long as or equalling the lamina; lamina oblong-lanceolate, deeply cordate and auricled at the base; auricles of young leaves rounded, those of mature leaves triangular, more or less lobed, sometimes projecting horizontally for 3-4 cm and leaves then hastate. Sori elliptical, shorter and wider than in {\b 29}. 2n = 72.{\i  Moist, shady calcareous rocks. Mediterranean region}. Bl Co Ga Gr Hs It Ju Sa Si.
