\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 31. A. hybridum} (Milde) Bange,{\i  loc. cit.} (1952) ({\i Phyllitis hybrida} (Milde) C. Chr.,{\i  Phyllitopsis hybrida} (Milde) Reichstein). Leaves up to 12 × 2 cm, the petiole about 1/2 as long as the lamina; lamina oblong-lanceolate, obtuse, irregularly pinnatifid and often with rounded auricles at the base, not deeply cordate. Sori narrowly elliptical to broadly ovate. 2n = 144.{\i  Calcareous rocks and walls. • Islands of N.W. Jugoslavia}. Ju.
